<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Void is the easiest of the data types to explain. Basically,
void means â€œno typeâ€. Consequentially, variables can not be defined with a type
of void.</p>

<div class="language-cpp highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="kt">void</span> <span class="n">value</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="c1">//won't work, variables can't be defined with a void type</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<ol>
  <li>The function of void is the similar to zero.</li>
</ol>

